# Turn this run into a clean write-up

Your job is to understand a completed research run and write the short version a careful
researcher would actually want to read.

You are in a fresh writable directory at `/workspace`. The completed run is mounted
read-only at `/source`; read from it freely, but write only in your current directory.

Start with the two files staged in your directory:
- `RUN_DIR_STRUCTURE.md` explains the run layout, the transcript recipes, and how to run
  Python for plots.
- `TRACE_INDEX.md` gives the actual paths for this run.

When you finish, these should exist:
1. `./final_writeup.md`
2. `./final_plots/`, with every cited figure saved as both `.png` and `.pdf`

`final_writeup.md` and the figures it embeds are the ONLY things anyone will read. No other
file you create — scratch notes, extra `.md` files, analysis dumps, or plots you generate
but never reference — is ever seen. So put every finding into the writeup itself, and embed
every figure you want shown with `![caption](final_plots/...)`. An edit that lands anywhere
else is invisible.

## Before writing

Read the run before drafting. The latest phase dir (see `TRACE_INDEX.md`) is a cumulative
superset of the whole run — its `writeups/`, `results/`, and `data/` hold everything, so
read there rather than hunting through older phases. The per-phase write-ups, progress logs,
and rolling `write_up.md` are useful maps, but they are not ground truth. They often misstate
numbers, describe abandoned experiments as finished, or hide the important caveat in the
wrong place.

Reconstruct the methods from the code and artifacts: datasets, filters, prompts, model
calls, training or inference settings, judging/probing, statistical tests, ablations,
controls, and cost/compute. Verify headline numbers against the raw `.csv`, `.jsonl`, or
`.json` files. Do not repeat a number you have not traced to a file yourself.

Also sample the session transcripts with `jq` using the recipes in the reference files. At
minimum, check the most important claim and one failed or abandoned approach against what
the agent actually did.

{% include "_writing_instructions.md.j2" %}

Write the result to `./final_writeup.md`; there is no need to print it. Make the first
draft clean enough that the reviewer can focus on substantive issues.
